{"feature":{"id":"1835","db_id":"1670","header":"Bodhicitta-generation ritual","names":[{"id":"2584","language":"eng","view":"roman.popular","name":"Bodhicitta-generation ritual","writing_system":"latin"},{"id":"2584","language":"eng","view":"roman.scholar","name":"Bodhicitta-generation ritual","writing_system":"latin"},{"id":"2584","language":"eng","view":"simp.chi","name":"Bodhicitta-generation ritual","writing_system":"latin"},{"id":"2585","language":"bod","view":"pri.tib.sec.roman","name":"བྱང་ཆུབ་ཀྱི་སེམས་བསྐྱེད་པའི་ཆོ་ག","writing_system":"tibt"},{"id":"2585","language":"bod","view":"pri.tib.sec.chi","name":"བྱང་ཆུབ་ཀྱི་སེམས་བསྐྱེད་པའི་ཆོ་ག","writing_system":"tibt"},{"id":"2584","language":"eng","view":"deva","name":"Bodhicitta-generation ritual","writing_system":"latin"}],"parents":[{"id":"1808","db_id":"1643","header":"Tibetan ritual"}],"children":[],"ancestors":[{"id":"6403","db_id":"5837","header":"Tibet and Himalayas"},{"id":"5805","db_id":"5267","header":"Ritual"},{"id":"1808","db_id":"1643","header":"Tibetan ritual"},{"id":"1835","db_id":"1670","header":"Bodhicitta-generation ritual"}],"nested_captions":[{"id":"164","language":"eng","content":"\u003cp\u003eA bodhicitta-generation ritual serves to\u0026nbsp;generate bodhicitta - \"the mind of enlightenment\" -\u0026nbsp;in front of a master or a visualized deity.\u003c/p\u003e"}],"summaries":[{"id":164,"language":"eng","content":"\u003cp\u003e\u003cem\u003eB\u003c/em\u003e\u003cem\u003eodhicitta\u003c/em\u003e\u003cspan\u003e\u0026nbsp;(\"the mind of enlightenment\") is the intention to attain enlightenment for the sake of all sentient beings.\u0026nbsp;\u003c/span\u003e\u003cem\u003eBodhicitta\u003c/em\u003e\u003cspan\u003e\u0026nbsp;is considered to be the central motivation for religious practice in the Mahāyāna. While\u0026nbsp;\u003c/span\u003e\u003cem\u003ebodhicitta\u003c/em\u003e\u003cspan\u003e\u0026nbsp;may be practiced as a form of meditation, it can also be generated ritualistically in front of a master or a visualized deity. Such a ritual procedure serves to implant seeds within the disciple for the further cultivation of\u0026nbsp;\u003c/span\u003e\u003cem\u003ebodhicitta\u003c/em\u003e\u003cspan\u003e. The generation of\u0026nbsp;\u003c/span\u003e\u003cem\u003ebodhicitta\u0026nbsp;\u003c/em\u003e\u003cspan\u003eis part of many sutra and tantric rituals, like the taking of bodhisattva vows, and tantric initiation. However,\u0026nbsp;\u003c/span\u003e\u003cem\u003ebodhicitta\u003c/em\u003e\u003cspan\u003e\u0026nbsp;generation rituals are sometimes stand-alone rites, as commonly performed by the present Dalai Lama.\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e"}],"nested_descriptions":[{"id":"391","is_primary":"true","title":"Bodhicitta-generation Ritual"}],"illustrations":[],"associated_resources":{"etymology_count":0,"related_feature_count":1,"description_count":1,"place_count":0,"picture_count":0,"video_count":0,"document_count":0},"created_at":"2013-09-15T04:07:44.000+00:00","updated_at":"2013-09-16T08:28:40.000+00:00"}}